text: Notes from today's discussion. Action Items near the top. <https://docs.google.com/a/uncorkedstudios.com/document/d/1AbFAt-6WOTc8WLECb2S4P1GPuFB-YNk6l4Ds21GJBGk/edit?usp=sharing>
Been crunching some numbers in our spreadsheet based on Riverwood’s additional estimates - Looks like our ask should be closer to $2mil than 1.25mil.
is that the number for collected knowns but not unknowns, or does it include some planning for unknowns?

It has some slop for resources that are unknowns (like data science, sales, customer support) that we might not need this calendar year. It has some padding on our current riverwood estimates, and we’re using the highest range on their costs.

Also assumptive (but not presumptive) is a cost plus rate for Uncorked. It may make more sense to shift web dev + mobile dev to Sommely only resources at a lower cost. (Mainly bc the scale of the Uncorked resources is around 7,000 hours)

Has travel and legal budgets and there might be some overlap between our low production run costs + assembly and some of the Riverwood numbers. But if we want to be safe and pad this by 20% right now - add another $400k or so for the unknown unknowns.
We could go with cheaper tooling and eat into this quite considerably - so there are a number of levers that still need to be pulled.

Oddly satisfying google search led to this comprehensive guide to grasping forces: <https://www.researchgate.net/publication/228912121_Study_of_the_Influence_of_Varying_Diameter_and_Grasp-Forces_on_Mechanical_Impedance_for_the_Grasp_of_Cylindrical_Objects>
